remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-102">Le strisce o bande sono intervalli orizzontali o verticali che applicano un'ombreggiatura lo sfondo di un grafico a intervalli regolari o personalizzati.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-102">Strip lines, or strips, are horizontal or vertical ranges that shade the background of a chart in regular or custom intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-103">È possibile utilizzare le strisce per:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-103">You can use strip lines to:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1d757-104">Migliorare la leggibilità per la ricerca di singoli valori nel grafico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-104">Improve readability for looking up individual values on the chart.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1d757-105">Separare i punti dati durante la lettura del grafico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-105">Separate data points when reading the chart.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1d757-106">Evidenziare date che ricorrono a intervalli regolari, ad esempio, per identificare i dati del fine settimana fa riferimento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-106">Highlight dates that occur at regular intervals, for example, to identify weekend data points.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1d757-107">Evidenziare un intervallo chiave specifico dei dati.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-107">Highlight a specific key range of data.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1d757-108">Aggiungere una linea di soglia su un valore costante specifico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-108">Add a threshold line at a specific constant value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-109">Un singolo <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> è possibile disegnare una sola volta o più volte, un intervallo specificato dell'oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-109">A single <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> object can either be drawn once, or repeatedly, for a given interval.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-110">Questa azione è controllata dal <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-110">This action is controlled by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-111">Quando viene assegnato un valore pari a -1 per il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> proprietà, una rimuovere riga verrà disegnata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-111">When a value of -1 is assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property, one strip line will be drawn.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-112">Quando viene assegnato un valore diverso da zero al <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> proprietà, verrà disegnata una striscia ripetutamente ogni intervallo specificato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-112">When a non-zero value is assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property, a strip line will be drawn repeatedly at each given interval.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-113">Il percorso in cui viene disegnata una striscia viene influenzato anche dalle <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffset%2A> e <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffsetType%2A> le proprietà della striscia.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-113">The location where a strip line is drawn is also affected by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffset%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffsetType%2A> properties of the strip line.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-114">Le strisce sono sempre associate con un <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis> oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-114">Strip lines are always associated with an <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-115">Possono essere aggiunti in fase di progettazione e fase di esecuzione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-115">They can be added at both design time and run time.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-116">Per aggiungere una riga orizzontale o verticale per visualizzare una determinata soglia, impostare il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> proprietà su un valore pari a 0,0.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-116">To add a horizontal or vertical line to display a threshold, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property to a value of 0.0.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-117">Ciò comporterà una riga da disegnare.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-117">This will result in a line being drawn.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-118">È possibile usare la <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderDashStyle%2A> e <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderWidth%2A> le proprietà per il colore, larghezza e lo stile della linea.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-118">You can use the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderDashStyle%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderWidth%2A> properties for the color, width and style of the line.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-119">Nessuna proprietà dello sfondo del grafico (`Back*`) vengono utilizzati quando le <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> è impostata su 0,0.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-119">No chart background properties (`Back*`) are used when the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property is set to 0.0.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-120">Usare il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Text%2A> proprietà della striscia per associare una striscia del testo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-120">Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Text%2A> property of the strip line to associate text with a strip line.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-121">La selezione host e l'orientamento del testo può essere controllati dal <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.TextAlignment%2A> proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-121">The placement and orientation of this text can be controlled by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.TextAlignment%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-122">Quando sono definite più le strisce per lo stesso asse, è possibile che le strisce verranno si sovrappongano.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-122">When multiple strip lines are defined for the same axis, it is possible that the strip lines will overlap.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-123">L'ordine Z del <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> oggetti è determinata dall'ordine di occorrenza nel <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLinesCollection> oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-123">The Z-order of <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> objects is determined by their order of occurrence in the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLinesCollection> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-124">Ciò significa che la prima occorrenza è quello disegnata per primo; la seconda occorrenza viene disegnata in secondo luogo, e così via.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-124">This means that the first occurrence is drawn first; the second occurrence is drawn second, and so on.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-125">Le strisce non sono supportate per i tipi di grafico seguenti: grafici a torta, ad anello, a imbuto, a piramide, Kagi, ThreeLineBreak, PointAndFigure, polare e Radar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-125">Strip lines are not supported for the following chart types: Pie, Doughnut, Funnel, Pyramid, Kagi, ThreeLineBreak, PointAndFigure, Polar and Radar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-126">Esempio di codice seguente illustra tre applicazioni delle strisce.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-126">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-127">Le strisce orizzontali, prima vengono aggiunti a intervalli regolari.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-127">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-128">Le strisce verticali, secondo vengono aggiunti per evidenziare i dati del fine settimana punti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-128">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-129">Infine, viene aggiunto una striscia non ricorrenti per indicare la media dei punti dati della prima serie del grafico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-129">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()  
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
        ' Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter   
        stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red)   
  
        ' Add the strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1)   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.   
    Private Sub HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
        ' Set strip line to highlight weekends   
        Dim stripLine2 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold)   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
        stripLine2.Interval = 1   
        stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks   
        stripLine2.StripWidth = 2   
        stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2)   
  
        ' Set the axis label to show the name of the day   
        ' This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd"   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the mean value of the first series.  
    Private Sub AddThresholdStripLine()   
        Dim stripLine3 As New StripLine()   
  
        ' Set threshold line so that it is only shown once   
        stripLine3.Interval = 0   
  
        ' Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series   
        stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series(0).Name)   
  
        stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen   
        stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25   
  
        ' Set text properties for the threshold line   
        stripLine3.Text = "Mean"   
        stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3)   
    End Sub   
End Class  
```  
  
```csharp  
public partial class StripLines : System.Web.UI.Page   
    {  
        protected void Page_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)  
        {              
            // Add chart data  
            AddChartData();  
  
            // Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.  
            AddHorizRepeatingStripLines();  
  
            // Highlights weekend points using strip lines.  
            HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines();  
  
            // Adds a threshold line using strip lines.  
            AddThresholdStripLine();  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddChartData()  
        {  
            // Declare new random variable  
            Random rand = new Random();  
  
            // Add a week of data  
            for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++)   
            {  
                chart1.Series[0].Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.Next(20,35));  
            }  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()  
        {  
            // Instantiate new strip line  
            StripLine stripLine1 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine1.StripWidth = 0;  
            stripLine1.BorderColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BorderWidth = 3;  
            stripLine1.Interval = 5;  
  
            // Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter  
            stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red);  
  
            stripLine1.BackSecondaryColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BackGradientStyle = GradientStyle.LeftRight;  
  
            // Add the strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1);  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()  
        {  
            // Set strip line to highlight weekends  
            StripLine stripLine2 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold);              
            stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5;  
            stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
            stripLine2.Interval = 1;  
            stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks;  
            stripLine2.StripWidth = 2;  
            stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2);  
  
            // Set the axis label to show the name of the day  
            // This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd";  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
        /// value of all data points in the first series of the chart.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddThresholdStripLine()  
        {  
            StripLine stripLine3 = new StripLine();  
  
            // Set threshold line so that it is only shown once  
            stripLine3.Interval = 0;  
  
            // Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series  
            stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series[0].Name);  
  
            stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen;  
            stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25;  
  
            // Set text properties for the threshold line  
            stripLine3.Text = "Mean";  
            stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3);  
        }  
    }  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-134">È possibile impostare questa proprietà su un valore ARGB (alfa, rosso, verde, blu) valido.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-134">You can set this property to any valid ARGB (alpha, red, green, blue) value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-135">Per impostare una sfumatura per la striscia, impostare il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackColor%2A> e <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackSecondaryColor%2A> proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-135">To set a gradient for the strip line, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackColor%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackSecondaryColor%2A> properties.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-136">Se questo colore è impostato su "transparent", in altre parole, impostare il valore alfa su 0, non verrà assegnato nessun colore per lo sfondo dell'elemento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-136">If you set this color to "transparent"—in other words, set the alpha value to 0—no color will be assigned to the background of the element.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-137">Di conseguenza, lo sfondo sarà trasparente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-137">As a result, the background will be transparent.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-138">Se il <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> è impostata su 0.0, verrà tracciata una linea e <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A> proprietà determina il colore della linea, non di questa proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-138">If the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property is set to 0.0, a line will be drawn and the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A> property will determine the color of the line, not this property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1d757-139">Esempio di codice seguente illustra tre applicazioni delle strisce.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-139">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-140">Le strisce orizzontali, prima vengono aggiunti a intervalli regolari.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-140">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-141">Le strisce verticali, secondo vengono aggiunti per evidenziare i dati del fine settimana punti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-141">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1d757-142">Infine, viene aggiunto una striscia non ricorrenti per indicare la media dei punti dati della prima serie del grafico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1d757-142">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
        ' Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter   
        stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red)   
  
        ' Add the strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1)   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
        ' Set strip line to highlight weekends   
        Dim stripLine2 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold)   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
        stripLine2.Interval = 1   
        stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks   
        stripLine2.StripWidth = 2   
        stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2)   
  
        ' Set the axis label to show the name of the day   
        ' This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd"   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
    ''' value of all data points in the first series of the chart.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddThresholdStripLine()   
        Dim stripLine3 As New StripLine()   
  
        ' Set threshold line so that it is only shown once   
        stripLine3.Interval = 0   
  
        ' Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series   
        stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series(0).Name)   
  
        stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen   
        stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25   
  
        ' Set text properties for the threshold line   
        stripLine3.Text = "Mean"   
        stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3)   
    End Sub   
End Class  
